 the Baluch people living in the lower Helmand River Valley of Afghanistan. It is an area that has received little study since the early 20th Century, yet is a region with a remarkable history in one of the most volatile territories in the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aBaluchi (Southwest Asian people)zAfghanistanzHelmand River Valley. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aafghan institute of archaeology.  aafghan.  aafghanistan.  aanthropology.  aarchaeological mission.  aarchaeology.  abaluch people.  abiographical.  aclose knit communities.  acultural social.  aeconomic systems.  aengaging.  aenglish translation.  aethnographic monograph.  aextraordinary encounters.  afarsi.  ahelmand river valley.  ahistory.  alifetime.  apage turner.  apolitics.  arealistic.  aremarkable history.  aremote places.  arevolutionaries.  asistan region.  asocial science.  asouthwest afghanistan.  avillages.  avolatile territories.1 aAllen, Mitchell, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmiri, Babrak, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTrousdale, William B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311099769940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781800730434?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781800730434423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781800730434/original  a978-3-11-099769-9  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK